I loved using brie in a pizza. I made my own pizza dough and only spread a thin layer of Dijon over the crust. I would suggest that instead of cubing the cheese cutting it into thick slices, so it melts and covers the pizza more evenly. I also substituted fresh sage for the oregano. This recipie was absolutley delicious!

Rating: 3
Delicious. I use the fresh pizza dough from Trader Joe's and whatever mustards I have in the fridge - usually a mix of Mendocino hot & sweet and some kind of grainy dijon. Also - whatever ingredient from the onion family I have: shallots, red onions, vidalias, scallions. Finally, I peel, seed and coarsely chop the tomatoes. In other words, I use the recipe as a guide and have tried many of my own versions... and it's totally foolproof! TRY IT!

