I loved this! Took less than 30 min from start to finish. I used a foccacia dough which I already had in the fridge, rolled it out, and spread a thin layer of olive oil mixed with italian herbs before spreading on a thin layer of mustard. I followed the rest of the direcetions except substituted fresh sage for oregano and a Tbs garlic for onion and only used about 6 oz of brie which was plenty to please. My boyfriend loved it too!

